## SS 3. Write Comment (Post Pages)

🚨 Post comments use `<textarea name="body">` (NOT contenteditable). ALWAYS `JSON.stringify()` for text.
🚨 Navigate to `{post_url}/comments` FIRST — do NOT click "Comments" button (destroys evaluate context).

**Step 0 — Navigate to comments page:**
```
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"{post_url}/comments"}' 2>&1
```
Wait 3s (embed in next evaluate).

**Step 1 — Type + submit (ONE evaluate, textarea already visible):**

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));

    // Find textarea (already visible on /comments page)
    var ta = document.querySelector('textarea[name="body"]');
    if (!ta) return { error: 'no comment textarea found' };

    var text = ${JSON.stringify(commentText)};

    ta.focus();
    ta.value = text;
    ta.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
    ta.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));

    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));

    // Find "Post" submit button
    var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var submitBtn = btns.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Post' && !b.disabled);
    if (!submitBtn) {
      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));
      btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
      submitBtn = btns.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Post' && !b.disabled);
    }
    if (!submitBtn) return { typed: true, len: ta.value.length, error: 'no Post button' };
    submitBtn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true }));
    return { typed: true, submitted: true, len: ta.value.length };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

**Step 2 — Verify comment posted:**

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    var snippet = ${JSON.stringify(commentText.slice(0, 40))};
    var verified = document.body.innerText.includes(snippet);
    return { verified: verified };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

